cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with object detection and pose estimation using deep learning techniques. The use of laser scanners and dynamic occupancy grid maps (DOGMa) suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. However, the use of deep learning techniques and automatic label generation indicates that it could also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a loss function to counteract the high imbalance between mostly static background and extremely rare dynamic grid cells, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the development of an algorithm, which could place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the problem of misdetections, which could also place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
